# Azure AD Configuration
# These values come from your Azure AD app registration

# Required: Client ID from Azure AD app registration
AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id-here

# Required: Tenant ID for single-tenant apps, or 'common' for multi-tenant
# Single-tenant: Use your organization's tenant ID (GUID)
# Multi-tenant: Use 'common' to allow any Azure AD tenant
AZURE_TENANT_ID=common

# Optional: SharePoint site URL for team storage
# Default: /sites/root (root SharePoint site)
# Example: /sites/your-site-name
VITE_SHAREPOINT_SITE=/sites/root

# Optional: Edition setting for branding
# Values: 'licensed' (no branding, default for Azure)
# VITE_EDITION=licensed

# Azure AD App Registration Setup Instructions:
#
# 1. Go to Azure Portal > Azure Active Directory > App Registrations
# 2. Click "New registration"
# 3. Name: "VaRiScout Azure App"
# 4. Supported account types: Choose based on your needs:
#    - Single tenant: "Accounts in this organizational directory only"
#    - Multi-tenant: "Accounts in any organizational directory"
# 5. Redirect URI: Select "Single-page application (SPA)" and enter:
#    - Development: http://localhost:5173
#    - Production: https://your-domain.com
# 6. After registration, copy the "Application (client) ID" to AZURE_CLIENT_ID
# 7. Copy the "Directory (tenant) ID" to AZURE_TENANT_ID
#
# API Permissions Required:
# - Microsoft Graph > User.Read (Delegated)
# - Microsoft Graph > Files.ReadWrite (Delegated) - for OneDrive
# - Microsoft Graph > Sites.ReadWrite.All (Delegated) - for SharePoint
#
# All permissions are delegated (user consent), no admin consent required
# unless your organization has restricted user consent.
